The paper deals with two main topics: learning convex partitions and computing game theoretic equilibria. The first topic falls under the category of computational geometry and machine learning, which are covered by cs.CG and cs.LG respectively. The second topic falls under the category of game theory, which is covered by cs.GT. The paper also uses techniques from data structures (cs.DS), algorithms (cs.AL), information theory (cs.IT), and complexity theory (cs.CC). However, since the main focus of the paper is on game theory and computational geometry/machine learning, cs.GT and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CC, and cs.IT.
